  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Southern voices on HFC Bangladesh</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The implications of HFC for climate change will be better understood by Bangladesh civil society organisations, private sector and key government staff, opening space for advocacy and action towards phase-out of HFC</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;	Carry out a survey to generate data on trends in HFC consumption.
&#x2022;	Carry out desk research on the alternatives to HFC including to possibilities for retrofitting of existing appliances. 
&#x2022;	Engage with the ODS cell in the DoE under MOEF to assess the preparation for CoP and MoP to be held in Kigali in October 2016 and raise awareness of the negotiators.
&#x2022;	Raise awareness with NGO, CSO&#x2019;s and INGOs and the civil society as whole through FGDs and KIIs and by engaging electronic and print oint media including through consultative meetings with journalists to assist them in explaining and highlighting the importance of HFC phase-out. 
&#x2022;	Consult major importers of HFC, air conditioning equipment and chillers as well as air-condition assembling industry regarding reduction of HFC use a
&#x2022;	Hold a final workshop on the issue with all the stakeholders mentioned above.
&#x2022;	Based on the above map out a future strategy for civil society advocacy on HFC phase out.</narrative>
  </description>
